'''''2012: Time for Change''''' is a 2010 feature-length [[documentary film]] directed by João G. Amorim. Based in part on the books of [[Daniel Pinchbeck]], it premiered on April 9, 2010 at the Lumiere Theater in [[San Francisco]]. The film presents a positive alternative to apocalyptic doom and gloom, and features, among others, [[David Lynch]], [[Sting (musician)|Sting]], [[Ellen Page]], [[Gilberto Gil]], [[Barbara Marx Hubbard]], [[Michael_K._Dorsey|Michael Dorsey]] and [[Paul Stamets]].

