{{Infobox power station | name = | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Ontario | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|45|24|30|N|76|16|30|W|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | country = Canada | location = | status = | construction_began = | commissioned = | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = | operator = | solar_type = | ps_units_operational = | solar_csp_heliostats = | ps_electrical_capacity = | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | website = | extra = }}
The '''Arnprior Solar Project''' is a 23.4 [[Megawatt|MW]] [[solar farm]] located near the town of near [[Arnprior, Ontario|Arnprior]], [[Ontario]], [[Canada]]. It was developed and is owned by EDF EN Canada and is operated by EDF Renewable Services, both units of [[EDF Energies Nouvelles]]. Construction began in May 2009 and operation commenced in December 2009.
The project consists of 312,000 PV [[thin film solar cell|thin film solar panels]] made by [[First Solar]] and mounted on 13,000 fixed-tilt racks in a {{convert|200|acre}} field.
