'''Gundlakamma Reservoir Project''' is an irrigation project located in [[Prakasam district]] in [[Andhra Pradesh]], [[India]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindu.com/2008/01/29/stories/2008012958570300.htm |title=Andhra Pradesh / Ongole News : Inauguration of Gundlakamma project gets delayed |publisher=The Hindu |date=2008-01-29 |accessdate=2013-10-19}}</ref> The dam with 56 million cubic meters live storage capacity is located across the [[Gundlakamma River]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://india-wris.nrsc.gov.in/wrpinfo/index.php?title=Gundlakamma_Reservoir_D00587|title= Gundlakamma Reservoir D00587|accessdate=19 July 2015}}</ref>  It now supplies 100 acres out of the total envisaged area of 80,000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindu.com/2008/03/26/stories/2008032652500300.htm |title=Andhra Pradesh / Ongole News : Gundlakamma project inauguration tomorrow |publisher=The Hindu |date=2008-03-26 |accessdate=2013-10-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.in/2004/08/19/stories/2004081902151900.htm |title=The Hindu Business Line : Gundlakamma project gets green signal |publisher=Thehindubusinessline.in |date=2004-08-19 |accessdate=2013-10-19}}</ref> This reservoir also supplies drinking water to the nearby [[Ongole]] city.

