{{Infobox power station | name = Hoya de Los Vicentes Solar Plant | name_official = Parque Solar Hoya de Los Vicentes | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | location_map = Spain | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = <!-- {{coord| | |region:ES_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> | country = Spain | location = [[Jumilla]], [[Region of Murcia|Murcia]] | status = Operational | construction_began = | commissioned = 2008 | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = [[Elecnor]] | operator = | solar_type = [[Photovoltaics|Flat-panel PV]] | ps_units_operational = 120,000 | ps_electrical_capacity = 23&nbsp;MW | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | website = }}
The '''Hoya de Los Vicentes Solar Plant''' ({{lang-es|'''Parque Solar Hoya de Los Vicentes'''}}) is a [[photovoltaic power station]] in [[Jumilla]], [[Region of Murcia|Murcia]] in [[Spain]]. The solar park covers area of some {{convert|100|ha}} and comprises a group of 200&nbsp;[[photovoltaic array]]s with a total capacity of 23&nbsp;MW. A total of 120,000&nbsp;[[solar panel]]s have been installed in the facility.<ref>[http://www.exenewable.com/projectProfile.asp?id=12615 eXenewable Project Profile Page - Hoya de Los Vicentes, PV, Spain]</ref> The project generates energy equivalent to the annual consumption of 20,000&nbsp;households.
