The '''Pagami Creek Fire''' was a [[wildfire]] in Northern [[Minnesota]], United States, that began with a [[lightning]] strike on August 18, 2011.<ref name=inciweb/> After weeks of slow growth, the wildfire quickly spread to over {{convert|92000|acre|km2}} during several days of hot, dry, windy weather in mid-September.<ref>{{citation|title=Pagami Creek Wildfire |date=December 2011 |publisher=Superior National Forest |url=http://www.fs.usda.gov/Internet/FSE_DOCUMENTS/stelprdb5346343.pdf |format=PDF |accessdate=2012-01-15}}</ref> The fire spread beyond the [[Boundary Waters Canoe Area Wilderness]] to threaten homes and businesses.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lakelandtimes.com/main.asp?SectionID=9&SubSectionID=9&ArticleID=13839|title=Boundary Waters fire threatening homes, cabins|author=Douglas Etten|publisher=[[Lakeland Times]]|date=2011-09-13|accessdate=2011-09-13}}</ref> Smoke from the fires drifted east and south as far as the [[Upper Peninsula of Michigan]], [[Ontario]], and [[Chicago]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://toronto.ctv.ca/servlet/an/local/CTVNews/20110913/smoke-ontario-forest-fire-minnesota-110913/20110913/?hub=TorontoNewHome|title=Ont. smells smoke from Minnesota forest fire|publisher=[[CTV Toronto]]|date=2011-09-13|accessdate=2011-09-13}}</ref>

